<section id="grid-system">
  {{#if meta.description}}
    <div class="page-header">
      <p class="lead">{{{meta.description}}}</p>
    </div>
  {{/if}}

  <h2>Default fluid width grid</h2>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
    <div class="span1">1</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span4">4</div>
    <div class="span4">4</div>
    <div class="span4">4</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span4">4</div>
    <div class="span8">8</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span6">6</div>
    <div class="span6">6</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span12">12</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="span4">
      <p>The default grid system provided is a <strong>12-column grid with fluid widths</strong>. We do not use the Twitter Bootstrap fixed width classes.</p>
      <p>As shown here, a basic layout can be created with two "columns," each spanning a number of the 12 foundational columns we defined as part of our grid system.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="span4">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
  &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="span8"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="span4">
      <p>The main application has three responsive layout variations for various devices and resolutions: large widescreen desktops, devices with a width less than 768px, and devices with a width less than 480px. See the <a href="#Styleguide/docs/base-responsive">Responsive design</a> page for more information.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Offsetting columns</h2>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span4">4</div>
    <div class="span4 offset4">4 offset 4</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span3 offset3">3 offset 3</div>
    <div class="span3 offset3">3 offset 3</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
    <div class="span8 offset4">8 offset 4</div>
  </div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
  &lt;div class="span4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="span4 offset4"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

  <h2>Nesting columns</h2>
  <div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="span6">
      <p>With the static (non-fluid) grid system, nesting is easy. To nest your content, just add a new <code>.row</code> and set of <code>.span*</code> columns within an existing <code>.span*</code> column.</p>
      <h4>Example</h4>
      <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
        <div class="span6">
         Level 1 of column 1
          <div class="row-fluid show-grid">
            <div class="span6">
             Level 2
            </div>
            <div class="span6">
             Level 2
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="span6">
         Level 1 of column 2
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="span6">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
  &lt;div class="span6"&gt;
    Level 1 of column 1
    &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
      &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Level 2&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="span6"&gt;Level 2&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="span6"&gt;
    Level 1 of column 2
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Grid customization</h2>
  <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Variable</th>
        <th>Default value</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@gridColumns</code></td>
        <td>12</td>
        <td>Number of columns</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@fluidGridColumnWidth</code></td>
        <td>6.382978723%</td>
        <td>Width of each column</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>@fluidGridGutterWidth</code></td>
        <td>2.127659574%</td>
        <td>Negative space between columns</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="span6">
      <h3>Variables in LESS</h3>
      <p>Built in are a handful of variables for customizing the default fluid grid system, documented above. All variables for the grid are stored in <code>styleguide/less/fixed_variables.less</code> or <code>styleguide/less/</code></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Fluid layout</h2>
  <div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="span6">
      <p><code>&lt;div class="container-fluid"&gt;</code> gives additional padding around the row-fluid containers. It's great for apps and docs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="span6">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div class="container-fluid"&gt;
  &lt;div class="row-fluid"&gt;
    &lt;div class="span8"&gt;
      &lt;!--Body content--&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="span4"&gt;
      &lt;!--Sidebar content--&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
